# Tracking marker — NOT used at build or runtime.
#
# This records the balena CLI version that balenamcp's wrapped command surface
# (the argv every tool constructs) has been verified against. balena-cli is
# shelled out at runtime, so it is neither a go.mod dependency nor a GitHub
# Action `uses:` line — only a Renovate customManager (see renovate.json) sees
# this line. Renovate opens a `chore(deps)` PR whenever balena-cli publishes a
# newer npm release; its PR body carries the upstream changelog.
#
# Review each such PR for parameter drift — renamed/removed subcommands or
# flags in the commands we wrap — using the balena-cli-parity agent, and merge
# it only once the new version is confirmed clean. Merging is the record that
# the new CLI has been reviewed.
BALENA_CLI_VERSION=25.1.10
